blaws
OBJ Modeler

Physics modeler for .obj files. C++ with GLUT/OpenGL on Mac OSX.

Compilation: 'make'
Execution: './modeler -o <obj file>'
Optional arguments: -s <scale factor>
		    -x <x-translation>
		    -y <y-translation>
		    -z <z-translation>
		    -X <x-rotation>
		    -Y <y-rotation>
		    -Z <z-rotation>
		    -g <gravity (0-6)
		    -c <connection level (0-3)>
		    -n <# Verlet repetitions>

Controls:
Left mouse button drag - rotate view (virtual trackball scheme)
Right-click - poke/pin/delete vertex (see 'p' and 'd')
'i', 'o' - zoom in/out
'c' - toggle between poking nearest vertex and all vertices
'w' - cycle wind speed
'g' - cycle gravity strength
'f' - toggle friction
'0', '1', '2', '3' - set connection level
'p' - toggle pin mode
'u' - unpin all vertices
'd' - toggle delete mode
'-', '=' - increase/decrease poke force
',', '.' - increase/decrease number of Verlet repetitions
'r' - reset model
Up/Down - move view vertically
Enter - toggle wireframe view
